CatDescriptText: Cutline of article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 9, 1941, pg. 3 reads: "James Weldon Johnson Camp Model Project - Above are scenes from Camp James Weldon Johnson, situated on Raccoon Creek in foothills of the beautiful Allegehney [Allegheny] mountains just 34 miles from Pittsburg. Some of the children who enjoyed the facilities of the spacious grounds during the past two weeks are pictured."
TitMainTitle: Group of boys and girls standing in water holding hands beside dock, with boy wearing bathing suit and light colored hat standing on dock, at Camp Weldon Johnson, Beaver County, Pennsylvania
